    "titles": {
      "en": "Overcoming adversaries through awe-inspiring presence"
    },
    "verse_count": 2,
    "verse_start_index": 1883,
    "verse_translations": [
      "en.sayed-ali-raza"
    ],
    "verses": [
      {
        "index": 1884,
        "local_index": 1,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "٣١٨. وَقِيلَ لَهُ (عليه ‏السلام): بِأَيِّ شَيْ‏ءٍ غَلَبْتَ الْأَقْرَانَ، فَقَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:201:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/318/392",
        "text": [
          " (عليه السلام): مَا لَقِيتُ رَجُلًا إِلَّا أَعَانَنِى عَلَى نَفْسِهِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "318. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, was asked: With what did you overpower your adversaries? He answered: Whenever I confronted a person he helped me against himself."
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1885,
        "local_index": 2,
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:201:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/318/393",
        "text": [
          "قال السيد الرضي: يومئ بذلك إلى تمكن هيبته فى القلوب."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "as-Sayyid ar-Raḍī says: Amīr al-mu’minīn is pointing out his striking of awe in the hearts. [1]"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
